data.enText: a school or college for special training

data.chText: （艺术、文学、科学等的）研究院，学会
data.enText: a type of official organization which aims to encourage and develop art, literature, science, etc.

data.chText: （苏格兰）中等学校；（美国）私立学校
data.enText: a secondary school in Scotland or a private school in the US

means: (艺术、文学、科学等的)研究院，学会

tr: a learned establishment for the advancement of knowledge
an institution for the advancement of art or science or literature

value.def: Academy is sometimes used in the names of schools and colleges, especially those specializing in particular subjects or skills, or private high schools in the United States.

example.ex: ...her experience as a police academy instructor.
example.tran: 她在警校当教官的经历

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft in names

value.tran: 专科院校;学院;(美国的)私立中学

value.def: Academy appears in the names of some societies formed to improve or maintain standards in a particular field.

example.ex: The British Academy of Film and Television Arts.
example.tran: 英国电影和电视艺术学院
